      "content": "I'm so sorry you're going through this. Losing someone after a decade is an incredibly heavy burden, and the way your mind works—forgetting and then remembering—is a common part of grief. It doesn't mean you're broken; it just means your heart is still holding on.\n\nYou don't have to figure out who you are \"without them\" right now. That identity can be rebuilt slowly, one day at a time, even if it feels impossible today. Would you like to talk about what you're feeling right now, or maybe share a memory of them that still feels important?",
