      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how exhausted and heavy you feel right now. It makes sense that you feel like everything is rubble; when the foundation of your life is gone, it's incredibly hard to see any point in rebuilding. The crushing weight you describe is a very real part of grief, and it's okay to feel like you don't have the strength to fight it today.\n\nYou don't have to force yourself to move forward or find meaning right this second. Sometimes, the only thing you can do is sit with the rubble and let yourself be tired. If you're up for it, I'm here to listen to whatever you need to say, whether it's about the plans that are gone or just the feeling of being too drained to speak.",
